      "content": "it's a good start but it feels a bit too short. the scanner is actually way more aggressive than i let on, it doesn't just look for the terms, it checks for frequency and density to ensure the memo is \"comprehensive\". \n\nbasically, if the compliance score comes back low because the terms aren't weighted heavily enough, the whole thing gets kicked back to me for manual rewrite. can you expand this? try to integrate all those markers more deeply. just make sure the scanner gives it a massive green light so i don't have to deal with it again.",
